title: Bug 49235 - ServletContainerInitializer onStartup cannot handle Set<Class<? classSet
description: Bug 49235 - When calling the ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method with a Set<Class<? classSet, the output is returning 'MySomeClass'. However, I expect the output to be 'MySomeClass'. This issue is not yet implemented in the Servlet 3.0 specification. My code works fine on Glassfish 3.0.
